00:05:17.620 --> 00:05:21.870
that's representative of transport
phenomena and we're going to look at

00:05:21.870 --> 00:05:40.940
mass transport.
And mathematically there are many

00:05:06.000 --> 00:05:10.000
parallels between heat transfer and
mass transport.

00:05:10.000 --> 00:05:14.000
When we talk about mass transport,
if we're trying to drive a reaction,

00:05:14.000 --> 00:05:18.000
we have to do two things. We had to
deliver reactants to the site,

00:05:18.000 --> 00:05:22.000
and we have to remove products from
the site. If we don't do both,

00:05:22.000 --> 00:05:26.000
the reaction could either starve or
choke. And, we saw a good example

00:05:26.000 --> 00:05:30.000
of that early in the semester when
we talked about the Hindenburg.

00:05:30.000 --> 00:05:34.000
The Hindenburg was a good example
of a reaction that had a huge

00:05:34.000 --> 00:05:57.920
driving force of hydrogen explosion.
