explosively, we would have had to

00:06:05.640 --> 00:06:09.490
deliver 7,000,
00 cubic feet of oxygen

00:06:09.490 --> 00:06:13.350
instantaneously.
And we couldn't do that.

00:06:13.350 --> 00:06:17.210
We could not do that, so because
the reaction was starved thanks to a

00:06:17.210 --> 00:06:21.070
transport phenomena problem,
instead of an explosion, what we got

00:06:21.070 --> 00:06:24.750
was a burn.
And, as a result,

00:06:24.750 --> 00:06:28.250
two thirds of the occupants of the
vessel were able to walk off it.

00:06:28.250 --> 00:06:31.750
And, not so many perished as
otherwise would have.

00:06:31.750 --> 00:06:35.250
So, transport phenomena,
clearly important. And, the

00:06:35.250 --> 00:06:38.750
dominant form of mass transport in
solids is diffusion.

00:06:38.750 --> 00:06:42.250
So, when we're talking about mass
transport in solids,

00:06:42.250 --> 00:06:45.750
we have to talk about diffusion.
And that's why we're going to do it.

00:06:45.750 --> 00:06:49.250
So, let's think of an example.
